                                    <watches>4</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="67837" author="jlevi" created="Fri, 27 Sep 2013 17:16:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch landed to Master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="67714" author="sarah" created="Thu, 26 Sep 2013 16:30:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After rebase on patch 7673, test passed&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7091/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7091/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="63488" author="sarah" created="Thu, 1 Aug 2013 17:47:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the patch is blocked by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3126&quot; title=&quot;conf-sanity test_41b: fld_server_lookup()) ASSERTION( fld-&amp;gt;lsf_control_exp ) failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3126&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3126&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="63081" author="adilger" created="Fri, 26 Jul 2013 21:27:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since we are already working on 2.5 it also makes sense to create an image from b2_4.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="63080" author="adilger" created="Fri, 26 Jul 2013 21:24:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7091&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/7091&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="63079" author="adilger" created="Fri, 26 Jul 2013 21:24:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Keith, the whole point of these test images is to allow testing that Lustre version X can mount and use filesystems that were formatted with Lustre version X-1, X-2, etc.  The only way to test such an upgrade is to actually format the filesystem with that earlier version of Lustre, and mount it with the current version of Lustre.  Doing that at runtime would be very complex, while creating static filesystem images with version X-1, X-2, (or version X for use in the future with X+1) is relatively easy.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="58664" author="keith" created="Thu, 16 May 2013 16:32:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there a reason we need multiple static image tarballs in test?  This seems like code bloat.  Sorry I don&apos;t know much about this specific test but this seems odd. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
